Huayu to Buy Assets From Chairman for HK$1 Billion

-- B y   J o s h u a   F e l l m a n
-- 
2011-04-12T14:34:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-12/huayu-to-buy-assets-from-chairman-for-hk-1-billion-correct-.html
(Corrects currency conversion in first paragraph.)  Huayu Expressway Group Ltd. (1823)  said it
will pay Chan Yeung Nam, its chairman and owner of a 73 percent
stake, HK$1 billion ($129 million) in the form of 780 million
new shares for Sumgreat Investments Ltd.  The target owns 10 companies that invest in, build, operate
and manage road projects and provide telecommunication
engineering services in  China , according to a Hong Kong stock
exchange filing today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Fellman at 
 jfellman@bloomberg.net  